WEBVTT

00:06.925 --> 00:10.011
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

01:16.828 --> 01:19.956
REBECCA: <i>My name is Rebecca Halliday.</i>
<i>I'm a litigator at Lowell Tiller.</i>

01:20.039 --> 01:24.169
<i>This is my deputy, Ross Kessler,</i>
<i>along with Ken Weinraub and Mark Gage.</i>

01:24.252 --> 01:27.213
Our firm has been hired by your employer,
Atlantis World Media,

01:27.297 --> 01:30.467
to represent them in a multimillion dollar
wrongful termination suit.

01:30.550 --> 01:33.928
This is not a formal proceeding.
You are not under oath.

01:34.012 --> 01:36.347
Your statements, however, will be recorded

01:36.431 --> 01:39.267
and a full report,
along with part or all of your statements,

01:39.350 --> 01:42.103
may be turned over to
the plaintiff as discovery.

01:42.187 --> 01:44.189
- Do you understand?
- Yes.

01:44.272 --> 01:46.191
REBECCA: This is gonna be simple.

01:46.274 --> 01:49.319
Your testimony revolves around two words.

01:49.402 --> 01:51.029
- It happened.
- It happened.

01:51.112 --> 01:52.781
- The general didn't say that.
- Okay.

01:52.864 --> 01:54.783
And even if he had,
he never said it on the tape.

01:54.866 --> 01:56.785
Whoa, there, little onion.

01:57.368 --> 01:58.620
Okay.

01:58.703 --> 02:00.246
Let me start with a really tough question

02:00.330 --> 02:02.749
and I want you
to take your time and think about it.

02:02.832 --> 02:04.459
- Are you ready?
- Yeah.

02:04.542 --> 02:06.294
- What's your name?
- I'm sorry?

02:06.377 --> 02:09.464
These guys need your full name, address,
and occupation for the records.

02:09.547 --> 02:10.632
Margaret Claire Jordan.

02:10.715 --> 02:13.301
344 East 75th Street, New York, New York.

02:13.384 --> 02:16.471
I'm an associate producer
with ACN, Atlantis Cable News.

02:16.554 --> 02:19.182
- Do you like the East Side?
- Yeah.

02:19.265 --> 02:21.142
I don't know.
I always thought the best thing about it

02:21.226 --> 02:22.644
was you got to look at the West Side.

02:22.727 --> 02:26.439
I'm on the third floor.
My window faces another window.

02:26.523 --> 02:30.735
I just got shown a place on 5th Avenue.
High floor, wraparound terrace.

02:30.819 --> 02:32.195
It was listed at 17 million,

02:32.278 --> 02:34.239
but the broker thinks it's gonna go
as low as 14.5.

02:34.322 --> 02:35.365
They're very motivated.

02:35.448 --> 02:37.700
I looked at the same place,
but I need a bigger ballroom.

02:37.784 --> 02:40.078
On March 22 of this year,

02:40.161 --> 02:41.996
you and Jerry Dantana
conducted an interview

02:42.080 --> 02:43.498
with General Stanislaus Stomtonovich.

02:43.581 --> 02:45.667
- Am I pronouncing the name correctly?
- Yes.

02:45.750 --> 02:48.294
- Those Dutch don't make it easy, do they?
- It's Polish.

02:48.378 --> 02:49.838
I know, but I just have
a thing about the Dutch.

02:49.921 --> 02:52.048
The interview was conducted at his home

02:52.131 --> 02:54.259
- in Silver Spring, Maryland?
- Yes.

02:54.342 --> 02:57.512
Every four years, we give
these guys a gold medal in "flukentot"

02:57.595 --> 02:59.639
when they grew up having
to "flukentot" to school.

02:59.722 --> 03:01.140
- Who?
- The Dutch.

03:01.224 --> 03:03.476
- I'm Dutch.
- Well, then fuck you.

03:04.853 --> 03:07.647
Look, it's not like I don't know
what this is gonna be about

03:07.730 --> 03:10.108
and I also understand the strategy

03:10.191 --> 03:11.860
of trying to rattle someone
before an interview.

03:11.943 --> 03:13.486
That's not what I'm doing.

03:13.570 --> 03:15.154
I'm trying to see if you laugh anymore.

03:17.365 --> 03:20.118
I make these guys laugh all the time. Don't I?

03:21.035 --> 03:23.580
I crack these guys up.

03:23.663 --> 03:26.541
I am known as a funny lawyer.
You should check me out.

03:26.624 --> 03:28.042
I have checked you out, Rebecca,

03:28.126 --> 03:29.878
and you don't handle
wrongful termination suits.

03:29.961 --> 03:31.713
- You're a First Amendment lawyer.
- I am.

03:31.796 --> 03:33.840
And I haven't read the other ones yet,
but they're on the list.

03:33.923 --> 03:38.678
Well, I'd like to once and for all
abudiate the notion that I am messed up.

03:38.761 --> 03:40.889
- Once and for all.
- I understand.

03:40.972 --> 03:42.932
- Thank you.
- But I'm gonna challenge you on "abudiate."

03:43.016 --> 03:45.226
- Yeah, there's no such word.
- Then why'd you use it?

03:45.310 --> 03:46.644
Because I am funny, too.

03:47.979 --> 03:52.108
We are going to expel or dismiss or expunge

03:52.191 --> 03:54.152
the notion that I am damaged.

03:54.235 --> 03:57.071
I'm hardly the only person in my newsroom
who's ever seen a dead guy.

03:57.155 --> 03:59.449
And that part of this case
would be hanging on my...

03:59.532 --> 04:01.534
- I don't know what to call it.
- State of mind.

04:01.618 --> 04:05.580
Seriously, that part of this case
would be hanging on my state of mind

04:05.663 --> 04:08.416
six months later, by the way,
when we interviewed Stomtonovich...

04:08.499 --> 04:10.543
- Dutch son of a bitch.
- ...is insane.

04:10.668 --> 04:12.337
- I'm not kidding.
- I know.

04:12.462 --> 04:14.005
I'm here to help you abudiate.

04:14.088 --> 04:15.924
- That's what we're doing this morning.
- Okay.

04:16.007 --> 04:18.092
So you're gonna have to tell me about Africa.

04:18.176 --> 04:20.094
The fact that you're even asking
implies that it's relevant.

04:20.178 --> 04:23.431
The fact that it's in Jerry Dantana's affidavit
implies it is relevant.

04:23.514 --> 04:27.060
He says that you were on prescription
medications when you came back from Africa,

04:27.143 --> 04:29.103
probably a series of SSRIs,

04:29.187 --> 04:31.105
- serotonin reuptake inhibitors.
- I wasn't.

04:31.189 --> 04:33.107
And that you're in no position

04:33.191 --> 04:35.944
- to say whether Stomtonovich said...
- It happened.

04:36.027 --> 04:37.695
- ...it happened.
- He didn't say it.

04:37.779 --> 04:40.615
What I would do if I were them
is I would put you in front of a jury

04:40.698 --> 04:42.241
and I would make you tell the Africa story

04:42.325 --> 04:45.119
and I would be good and sure
that you broke down while you were telling it.

04:45.203 --> 04:46.788
They're free to try.

04:46.871 --> 04:49.207
Well, I'd like to get
a first look at how it's gonna go.

04:50.625 --> 04:52.126
Gary Cooper and I flew to Uganda.

04:52.210 --> 04:54.629
Is his name really Gary Cooper?

04:54.712 --> 04:56.005
Yes.

04:56.255 --> 04:57.256
(REBECCA LAUGHS)

04:58.549 --> 05:02.053
I laugh every time I read that.
I can't wait to meet him.

05:02.887 --> 05:04.347
Why did you fly to Uganda?

05:04.430 --> 05:07.141
I pitched a story about
the 100 US combat troops

05:07.225 --> 05:08.893
that were sent to hunt for Joseph Kony,

05:08.977 --> 05:10.728
who's the leader of
the Lord's Resistance Army.

05:10.812 --> 05:12.522
In exchange for access to Camp Kasenyi,

05:12.605 --> 05:14.857
which is our forward
operating base out of Kampala,

05:14.941 --> 05:17.819
the Pentagon's Public Affairs people
wanted us to shoot some film

05:17.902 --> 05:19.946
of soldiers building
an addition onto an orphanage.

05:20.029 --> 05:22.281
That's a sad project when you think about it.

05:22.448 --> 05:24.367
Yeah, I could fall apart any second.

05:24.450 --> 05:26.494
I wasn't baiting you.

05:26.577 --> 05:28.997
When did you and Gary leave?

05:29.080 --> 05:31.374
A year ago September.
The night of September 30.

05:31.457 --> 05:33.459
How do you get to Uganda?

05:33.543 --> 05:34.836
Practice.

05:34.919 --> 05:38.214
You fly to Dubai
and get a connecting flight to Entebbe.

05:38.297 --> 05:41.050
We left straight
from the newsroom right before...

05:41.175 --> 05:42.176
(STIFLES LAUGH)

05:43.094 --> 05:45.471
Right before... God,

05:45.555 --> 05:47.849
right before Will

05:47.932 --> 05:51.352
just murderlized this woman from OWS.

05:51.436 --> 05:53.354
Gary and I watched it in the cab.

05:53.438 --> 05:55.523
<i>The new Fox News poll</i>
<i>has the former Massachusetts governor</i>

05:55.606 --> 05:58.568
<i>back in the lead with 23% of Republicans,</i>

05:58.651 --> 06:03.031
<i>followed by Rick Perry with 19%</i>
<i>and 17% for Herman Cain,</i>

06:03.114 --> 06:07.035
<i>reflecting a big boost</i>
<i>for the former Godfather's Pizza CEO.</i>

06:07.118 --> 06:10.288
<i>On the other side of the break,</i>
<i>I'll have one of the early organizers</i>

06:10.371 --> 06:11.914
<i>of the Occupy Wall Street movement.</i>

06:11.998 --> 06:13.708
<i>- We'll be right back.</i>
- Three minutes back.

06:13.791 --> 06:16.294
- We're leaving.
- Souvenirs, let's go. Shout them out.

06:16.377 --> 06:20.214
I would like any traditional tribal weapon,
short spears, hooks, sticks, bows.

06:20.298 --> 06:22.425
They're not gonna let them
pass security with short spears.

06:22.508 --> 06:24.510
And I'll have an intern get you local sticks.

06:24.594 --> 06:26.137
- Who's next?
- A silk kanzu.

06:26.220 --> 06:28.514
- That's a colorful wrap dress.
- Yeah.

06:28.639 --> 06:30.058
Got about two and a half minutes.

06:30.141 --> 06:32.351
I got a lot of friends
who think this is a bad idea.

06:32.435 --> 06:33.936
- How many?
- I don't know, a lot.

06:34.020 --> 06:35.354
It's just that it's a unit of measurement

06:35.438 --> 06:37.273
I hear invoked more and more.
"A lot of my friends."

06:37.356 --> 06:40.276
Mainstream media's been making us
look like idiots since this thing started.

06:40.359 --> 06:42.028
Don't refer to the mainstream media out there.

06:42.111 --> 06:44.405
It always sounds
like a losing team complaining about the ref.

06:44.489 --> 06:46.074
'Cause that's what
you always make it sound like.

06:48.326 --> 06:50.328
Excuse me. One second.

06:52.413 --> 06:54.082
MAN OVER PA: <i>Two minutes.</i>

06:54.832 --> 06:58.086
We've spidered every social networking site
and public board looking for Hamni8.

06:58.169 --> 07:01.172
We've sent an e-mail
to Hamni8 at every public domain,

07:01.255 --> 07:03.341
including the ISPs
most likely to service that region.

07:03.591 --> 07:05.760
We've got some bounce backs,
but no responses.

07:05.843 --> 07:07.386
We're out of here.

07:07.470 --> 07:09.263
What's going on?

07:09.347 --> 07:12.934
Late Wednesday night, they found a tweet
from a user in the area, Hamni8.

07:13.017 --> 07:14.811
A fast series of tweets
where he describes Genoa.

07:14.894 --> 07:17.063
- We think he's describing Genoa.
- JERRY: He is describing it.

07:17.146 --> 07:18.356
- Jesus.
- He's dead.

07:18.439 --> 07:20.733
- NEAL: We don't know that.
- What's the other option?

07:20.817 --> 07:23.486
- That he can't afford his cell plan anymore.
- Come on...

07:23.569 --> 07:26.114
In most of the developing world,
phones and plans are extremely expensive

07:26.197 --> 07:29.200
relative to income, and almost all are prepaid.
This was two years ago.

07:29.283 --> 07:31.661
He's standing there
describing gas being dropped on a village.

07:31.828 --> 07:34.247
Then the tweets stop and you think
it's because his cell plan ran out?

07:34.330 --> 07:36.624
Maybe they stopped then
because we were jamming their frequency.

07:36.707 --> 07:38.584
- I'm saying it's years later now...
- Fuck!

07:40.044 --> 07:42.380
- It's just gone.
- I need to get Shelly.

07:44.257 --> 07:45.800
It's time.

07:45.883 --> 07:47.468
What do we do now?

07:47.552 --> 07:50.012
Something's got to fall into our lap.

07:50.096 --> 07:53.141
Something's got to fall out of the sky
and right into our lap.

07:53.224 --> 07:55.476
A preposterous stroke of luck has to occur.

07:55.560 --> 07:56.894
Neal, I meant to tell you.

07:56.978 --> 07:59.313
A guy down at OWS
was telling a campfire story

07:59.397 --> 08:02.108
about working for an NGO
and getting the NGO shut down

08:02.191 --> 08:04.152
by the Pakistani government
because he wrote a report

08:04.235 --> 08:06.821
saying US troops
used chemical weapons on civilians.

08:06.904 --> 08:08.072
You should talk to him.

08:08.156 --> 08:09.615
You can just follow me, okay?

08:11.284 --> 08:13.578
- Wait, what?
- Did that just...

08:14.453 --> 08:16.747
Shelly, wait! Stop!

08:16.831 --> 08:20.168
- What did you say?
- The Pakistanis shut down the NGO.

08:20.251 --> 08:22.336
- She needs to be in the studio.
- No. What was the reason?

08:22.420 --> 08:25.590
He wrote a report that said US troops
were using chemical weapons.

08:25.673 --> 08:27.008
- What's his name?
- I don't know.

08:27.091 --> 08:28.509
Does he tend to hang out in the same place

08:28.593 --> 08:30.678
- in Zucotti Park every night?
- We are not hanging out.

08:30.761 --> 08:32.096
- Neal.
- I understand.

08:32.180 --> 08:33.306
Yes, he's in the same place every night.

08:33.389 --> 08:36.058
- Yes, I can take you there.
- Take her to the studio.

08:36.142 --> 08:37.810
This way.

08:40.938 --> 08:42.481
Okay. Okay.

08:43.232 --> 08:44.984
Thirty seconds back.

08:45.067 --> 08:47.195
And here comes dinner.

08:47.278 --> 08:49.322
- How you doing?
- Good, thank you.

08:49.405 --> 08:51.699
- Yeah, I got it.
- I'm sorry?

08:51.782 --> 08:53.534
I was talking to my producer.

08:53.618 --> 08:55.203
- How do I look?
- Good.

08:55.286 --> 08:57.246
No, producer again.

08:57.330 --> 08:59.123
Is he just screwing with her?

08:59.207 --> 09:02.627
- Come on.
- In three, two...

09:02.710 --> 09:05.546
<i>It's been two weeks</i>
<i>since a group of protesters</i>

09:05.630 --> 09:08.591
<i>began camping out</i>
<i>in Zucotti Park here in New York City.</i>

09:08.674 --> 09:11.510
<i>The Occupy Wall Street movement</i>
<i>has turned to social media</i>

09:11.594 --> 09:14.597
<i>and held marches</i>
<i>through the streets of the financial district.</i>

09:14.680 --> 09:16.974
<i>Here in the studio today is one of the leaders</i>

09:17.058 --> 09:19.143
<i>of Occupy Wall Street, Shelly Wexler.</i>

09:19.227 --> 09:20.770
- Don't take the bait.
<i>- Shelly, thanks for being with us.</i>

09:20.853 --> 09:23.397
<i>It's good to be here,</i>
<i>but I am not one of the leaders of OWS.</i>

09:23.481 --> 09:25.608
<i>- We don't have leaders.</i>
<i>- Is that a good idea?</i>

09:25.691 --> 09:28.194
- Not having leaders?
- Yeah.

09:28.277 --> 09:30.571
Yes, because this way,
everyone's sure to have a voice.

09:30.655 --> 09:32.573
Sounds like a lot of people talking at once.

09:32.657 --> 09:35.451
But tell us in a few words
what OWS is protesting.

09:35.534 --> 09:37.703
We are protesting a variety of issues,

09:37.787 --> 09:39.455
the co-opting of the government by the rich,

09:39.538 --> 09:43.626
the lack of any prosecution for the crimes
that led to the collapse of 2008,

09:43.709 --> 09:45.753
Citizens United, social inequality.

09:45.836 --> 09:47.129
So not any particular thing?

09:48.673 --> 09:50.299
Not one particular thing.

09:50.383 --> 09:51.926
You're protesting against lots of things?

09:52.009 --> 09:55.972
<i>The list of things we're protesting against</i>
<i>is as varied as the protesters themselves.</i>

09:56.055 --> 09:59.517
<i>I've seen protesters holding signs that say,</i>
<i>"We are the 99%."</i>

09:59.600 --> 10:01.394
<i>- Yes.</i>
<i>- I am the 1%.</i>

10:01.477 --> 10:04.063
Some people would say
I'm overpaid, but I'm not.

10:04.146 --> 10:06.148
I'm paid exactly what the market will bear,

10:06.232 --> 10:07.650
which means I'm paid what I'm worth.

10:07.733 --> 10:10.486
So which system would you
replace capitalism with?

10:12.488 --> 10:15.700
We wouldn't...
I wouldn't replace it with any system.

10:15.783 --> 10:17.368
I would make the system fairer.

10:17.451 --> 10:18.953
- By passing new laws?
- Yes.

10:19.036 --> 10:22.123
- It's Congress who does that.
- Yes.

10:22.206 --> 10:25.459
It's legislation like Dodd-Frank
that the banks really fear, right?

10:25.543 --> 10:26.585
Yes.

10:26.669 --> 10:28.129
If your congressman or your senator

10:28.212 --> 10:30.589
or the Chairman of the House
Financial Services Committee

10:30.673 --> 10:33.134
or the Speaker of the House
wanted to hear the demands

10:33.217 --> 10:35.803
of OWS, who would they meet with?

10:35.886 --> 10:37.805
We're not looking for a meeting.

10:37.888 --> 10:39.515
They wouldn't be able to
meet with anyone, right?

10:39.598 --> 10:40.599
<i>Look...</i>

10:40.683 --> 10:43.644
I'm trying to find the virtue
of a leaderless movement

10:43.728 --> 10:45.313
where everyone's voices are heard.

10:45.396 --> 10:46.856
<i>That isn't the point.</i>

10:46.939 --> 10:48.983
We want everyone to look
at Occupy Wall Street

10:49.066 --> 10:51.652
and ask themselves the question,
"Why is this happening?"

10:51.736 --> 10:53.487
I think that's been taken care of.

10:53.571 --> 10:56.407
But what happens after
people ask themselves that?

10:56.490 --> 10:57.992
<i>- Change, we hope.</i>
<i>- How?</i>

10:58.075 --> 11:00.036
<i>The same way change has always happened.</i>

11:00.119 --> 11:03.372
<i>What is your best-case scenario</i>
<i>for how this ends?</i>

11:04.206 --> 11:06.834
- That it doesn't end.
- Oh, God.

11:06.917 --> 11:08.544
<i>- That it doesn't end?</i>
<i>- That's right.</i>

11:08.627 --> 11:10.546
<i>Even if you put the heads of the banks in jail,</i>

11:10.629 --> 11:12.590
<i>overturn a Supreme Court decision,</i>

11:12.673 --> 11:15.343
ensure greater social equality
and give everybody money,

11:15.426 --> 11:17.887
you're still going to be
sleeping in Zucotti Park?

11:17.970 --> 11:21.140
Like most of the media,
I don't think you're taking this seriously.

11:21.223 --> 11:24.226
Is there any chance
that's because you're not?

11:25.853 --> 11:27.855
- Hey, it didn't go that badly.
- Fuck off!

11:27.938 --> 11:30.441
- Come on.
- I am humiliated and in shock.

11:30.524 --> 11:33.611
This whole thing is messed up
and he's a fucking asshole, by the way.

11:33.694 --> 11:34.779
He's not.

11:34.862 --> 11:37.156
Trying to be funny
at the expense of the guest.

11:37.239 --> 11:38.532
I don't think it was as bad as you think it was.

11:38.616 --> 11:39.867
Which way do I go to get out of here?

11:39.950 --> 11:41.619
- No. You need to take me to the guy.
- What?

11:41.702 --> 11:44.497
- The guy in the park.
- You think I'm disposed to doing you a favor?

11:44.580 --> 11:46.540
No, Shelly. Shelly, we need to meet this guy.

11:46.624 --> 11:48.250
- We need to read the report he wrote.
- No.

11:48.334 --> 11:49.460
- Shelly.
- Forget it.

11:49.543 --> 11:50.795
No, I can't tell you what this is about,

11:50.878 --> 11:52.630
but it's way too important
to use as a payback...

11:52.713 --> 11:54.882
I could have gone anywhere.
I did this as a favor to you.

11:54.965 --> 11:56.759
I need you to take me to this guy.

11:56.842 --> 11:58.219
Then we're both having a bad night.

11:58.302 --> 12:00.388
He didn't do anything to you. You tanked.

12:00.471 --> 12:01.722
(GRUNTS)

12:11.649 --> 12:13.150
She's gone.

12:54.316 --> 12:56.277
Good evening.
Welcome to the Radisson Concorde.

12:56.360 --> 12:58.446
Good evening.
We're with the Romney Press Corps.

12:58.529 --> 13:02.575
Three rooms under James Harper,
Hallie Shea and...

13:02.658 --> 13:04.910
You know what? I don't know your first name.

13:04.994 --> 13:06.579
- I'm sorry.
- Stillman's my first name.

13:06.704 --> 13:08.414
- Stillman's your first name?
- Yeah.

13:08.497 --> 13:09.874
- What's your last name?
- Frank.

13:09.957 --> 13:11.125
You sure it's not the other way around?

13:11.208 --> 13:13.002
It's three rooms. Harper, Frank, and Shea.

13:13.085 --> 13:15.129
I'm sorry, I'm not seeing anything.

13:15.212 --> 13:16.630
You said you were with the Romney bus?

13:16.714 --> 13:17.965
Yeah.

13:18.048 --> 13:20.050
The Romney Press Corps is all checked in.

13:20.885 --> 13:22.887
I understand what's happened.

13:22.970 --> 13:25.973
- We got off the Romney bus.
- 'Cause you said you were...

13:26.056 --> 13:28.309
Yeah, we're still covering
the campaign, we're just...

13:28.392 --> 13:31.437
It's not... We're staging a protest.

13:31.520 --> 13:33.731
I don't want to bore you with the details.

